{"title_page": "The Fairly OddParents (season 2)", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced|date=September 2009}}\n{{Infobox television season\n| season_number        = 2\n| bgcolour             = #edd073\n| image                = Numberjacks 0-9.jpg\n| image_alt            = \n| caption              = DVD cover\n| starring             = \n| country              = United States\n| num_episodes         = 15\n| network              = [[Nickelodeon]]\n| first_aired          = March 1, 2002\n| last_aired           = January 10, 2003\n| episode_list         = List of The Fairly OddParents episodes\n}}\n''[[The Fairly OddParents]]'' aired its second season starting on March 1, 2002. The season ended on January 10, 2003, production began from Fall of 2001 and concluded in the Summer of 2002.\n\n==Episodes==\n{{main|List of The Fairly OddParents episodes}}\n\n<onlyinclude>\n{{Episode table|background=#cce087|overall=5|season=5|title=22|director=20|writer=20|aux2=20|aux2T=Storyboard by|airdate=15|episodes=\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 8a\n |EpisodeNumber2= 1a\n |Title= Out for the Count\n |DirectedBy= [[Butch Hartman]]\n |WrittenBy= Butch Hartman & [[Steve Marmel]]\n |Aux2= Butch Hartman and<br />Paul McEvoy\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|3|1}} \n |ShortSummary=2 is out.\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 8b\n |EpisodeNumber2= 1b\n |Title= Hex Games\n |DirectedBy= Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Tim O'Rourke\n |Aux2= [[Bob Boyle (animator)|Bob Boyle]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|3|1}} \n |ShortSummary= Vicky, one of the best skaters at the skate park, is challenged by Timmy; if she wins, the skate park will have height limits on skateboarding, but if Timmy wins, the skate park will be open to all children.\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 9a\n |EpisodeNumber2= 2a\n |Title= Boy Toy\n |DirectedBy= Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Butch Hartman & Steve Marmel\n |Aux2= Butch Hartman and<br />Jim Schumann\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|3|8}} \n |ShortSummary= After Timmy wishes himself toy-sized to spend time with his old Crimson Chin action figure, Vicky's sister, Tootie, takes Cosmo and Wanda (disguised as dolls), and Timmy must go to Vicky and Tootie's house to find them.\n\n''Guest star:'' [[Jay Leno]] as the Crimson Chin\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 9b\n |EpisodeNumber2= 2b\n |Title= Inspection Detection\n |DirectedBy= Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Spencer Green<br />''Story by:'' Butch Hartman & Steve Marmel \n |Aux2= Butch Hartman\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|3|8}} \n |ShortSummary= Because Timmy wishes for things that were (coincidentally) stolen, Timmy is accused of shoplifting. Jorgen Von Strangle then comes for an inspection of Cosmo and Wanda, and if they fail, they will be taken away from Timmy. Meanwhile, Timmy is determined to catch the real shoplifter, Francis.\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 10a\n |EpisodeNumber2= 3a\n |Title= Action Packed\n |DirectedBy= John Fountain and<br />Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Tracy Berna and Steve Marmel\n |Aux2= John Fountain\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|3|22}} \n |ShortSummary= After watching an action-packed mystery movie, Timmy wishes for an action-packed life. However, it turns into terror when supervillain Jorgen captures Cosmo, Wanda, and all of the other fairies, and drains their magic out of them (\"[[Motion Picture Association of America film rating system#Ratings|PG-13]] horror\" as Timmy calls it, is shown for this part). Timmy must stop Jorgen before he becomes the mightiest fairy in the universe.\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 10b\n |EpisodeNumber2= 3b\n |Title= Smarty Pants\n |DirectedBy= John Fountain and<br />Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Tracy Berna \n |Aux2= John Fountain\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|3|22}} \n |ShortSummary= Timmy wishes he was the smartest kid in the world, but the situation becomes complicated when he is placed in a competition with A.J. and subsequently loses his intellect, since, according to \"The Rules\", fairy magic can't be used by humans to win competitions.\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 11a\n |EpisodeNumber2= 4a\n |Title= Timvisible\n |DirectedBy= Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Butch Hartman and Steve Marmel\n |Aux2= Butch Hartman and<br />Paul McEvoy\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|4|26}} \n |ShortSummary= On the last day of school, Timmy is getting the perfect attendance award, but Francis is celebrating the last day by beating up all the boys. In order to avoid getting beat up by Francis, Timmy wishes he was [[invisible]], but then has so much fun being invisible that he forgets about the awards ceremony. Now, he must rush to get his award, and avoid Mr. Crocker in the process, as he is trying to capture him because he could use him as proof that fairies exist. \n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 11b\n |EpisodeNumber2= 4b\n |Title= That Old Black Magic\n |DirectedBy= [[Sarah Frost]] and<br />Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Butch Hartman and Steve Marmel\n |Aux2= Jim Schumann, Butch<br />Hartman, and Sarah Frost\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|4|26}} \n |ShortSummary= On [[Friday the 13th]], Anti-Fairies cause trouble while the Turners spend the day at Adrenaland (a theme park filled with dangerous rides with a mascot known as Phen-Phen Phil).\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 12a\n |EpisodeNumber2= 5a\n |Title= Super Bike\n |DirectedBy= Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Jack Thomas\n |Aux2= Butch Hartman\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|5|10}} \n |ShortSummary= Timmy wishes up an indestructible bicycle, but the bike subsequently refuses to allow him to leave it.\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 12b\n |EpisodeNumber2= 5b\n |Title= A Mile in My Shoes\n |DirectedBy= [[Gary Conrad]] and<br />Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Tim O'Rourke, Butch Hartman, and Steve Marmel\n |Aux2= Chris Robertson\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|5|10}} \n |ShortSummary= Timmy has a rough day without his godparents by missing the bus to school, getting soaked in rain, and hit by volleyballs in gym class. Being jealous at his godparents for their wonderful lifestyle, Timmy becomes a fairy godparent while Cosmo and Wanda become ordinary children. However, Timmy finds out that being a godparent takes more responsibility.\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 13a\n |EpisodeNumber2= 6a\n |Title= Foul Balled\n |DirectedBy= John Fountain and<br />Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Butch Hartman and Steve Marmel\n |Aux2=\tChris Robertson and<br />John Fountain\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|6|7}} \n |ShortSummary= Timmy, tired of losing every game because of Chester, wishes that Chester would become a skilled [[baseball]] player, but Chester gets on Timmy's nerves when he starts hogging every position and shunning the rest of his team.\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 13b\n |EpisodeNumber2= 6b\n |Title= The Boy Who Would Be<br />Queen\n |DirectedBy= Sarah Frost and<br />Butch Hartman \n |WrittenBy= Steve Marmel and Butch Hartman\n |Aux2= Butch Hartman and<br />Sarah Frost\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|6|7}} \n |ShortSummary= Timmy accidentally wishes himself into a girl before Trixie's birthday party, and she uses her new feminine mind to get the perfect gift for her. However, it turns out that Trixie likes boy stuff, 