d, and Chad won because they bribed the judges. To make things worse, Vicky is being paid by Timmy's parents to take Timmy and his friends trick-or-treating, and forces him to wear a mummy costume made out of toilet paper. Vicky gets all of the candy, while Timmy and his friends get nothing. Realizing that Vicky is scary and gets more candy because of it, Timmy wishes that everyone's Halloween costumes were real and scary. This causes everyone to become real and scary versions of the costumes they wear, including the popular kids, who turn into the real Jack-O-Bots and threaten to destroy the world. Also, Timmy cannot undo the wish because Cosmo and Wanda were in costume at the time and are now no longer magical. Meanwhile, the Yugopotamians, seeing people celebrate Halloween, think Earth is planning an attack on them and attempt to counter-attack.\n\n''Guest star:'' [[Gilbert Gottfried]] as Dr. Bender & Wendell Bender\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 20a\n |EpisodeNumber2= 13a\n |Title= Ruled Out\n |DirectedBy= Gary Conrad\n |WrittenBy= Karin Gutman\n |Aux2= Dave Thomas\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|11|8}} \n |ShortSummary= Timmy, tired of his parents' strict rules, wishes for parents that cared less. However, when his mom and dad stop following the rules, and his new Fairy Godparents make things difficult, Timmy finds out why being responsible is important.\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 20b\n |EpisodeNumber2= 13b\n |Title= That's Life!\n |DirectedBy= Sarah Frost and<br />Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Spencer Green, Butch Hartman, and Steve Marmel\n |Aux2=\tButch Hartman and<br />Jim Schumann\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|11|8}} \n |ShortSummary= To help his Mom win the Dimmsdale \"Veg-off,\" Timmy wishes her garden full of life, but he does not remember that his dearly departed pet gerbil, Eddie, is buried in the garden, and wreaks havoc in Dimmsdale.\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 21a\n |EpisodeNumber2= 14a\n |Title= Shiny Teeth\n |DirectedBy= Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Butch Hartman and Steve Marmel\n |Aux2=\tHeather Martinez and<br />Butch Hartman\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|11|30}} \n |ShortSummary= Before his upcoming music video \"My Shiny Teeth and Me\", evil dentist Dr. Bender rips out Chip Skylark's teeth, which stops him from singing. Timmy must now contact the Tooth Fairy to seek aid in recovering Chip's teeth, and succeeds.\n\n''Guest stars:'' [[Chris Kirkpatrick]] as Chip Skylark & Skip Sparkypants and [[Gilbert Gottfried]] as Dr. Bender & Wendell Bender\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 21b\n |EpisodeNumber2= 14b\n |Title= Odd, Odd West\n |DirectedBy= John Fountain and<br />Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Steve Marmel and Jack Thomas\n |Aux2= Jim Schumann and<br />John Fountain\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|11|30}} \n |ShortSummary= Timmy and his friends visit the Old West and must face bandit Vicky.\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 22a\n |EpisodeNumber2= 15a\n |Title= Cosmo Con\n |DirectedBy= Wincat Alcala and<br />Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= [[Scott Fellows]] and Jack Thomas\n |Aux2= Wincat Alcala\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2003|1|10}} \n |ShortSummary= Cosmo has a chance to gain popularity when he is the next on the Fairy World List to host a Fairy Convention, but the convention turns out to be a destination alert when it happens in Timmy's bathroom while Crocker pays a visit.\n |LineColor=cce087\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fairly OddParents (season 2)\n |EpisodeNumber= 22b\n |EpisodeNumber2= 15b\n |Title= Wanda's Day Off!\n |DirectedBy= Sarah Frost and<br />Butch Hartman\n |WrittenBy= Jack Thomas\n |Aux2= Heather Martinez and<br />Shawn Murray\n 